{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Come with me to the bottom of the world,"},{"time":3000,"text":"Antarctica,"},{"time":5000,"text":"the highest, driest, windiest,"},{"time":7000,"text":"and yes, coldest region on Earth --"},{"time":10000,"text":"more arid than the Sahara"},{"time":12000,"text":"and, in parts, colder than Mars."},{"time":14000,"text":"The ice of Antarctica glows"},{"time":16000,"text":"with a light so dazzling,"},{"time":18000,"text":"it blinds the unprotected eye."},{"time":20000,"text":"Early explorers rubbed cocaine in their eyes"},{"time":22000,"text":"to kill the pain of it."},{"time":24000,"text":"The weight of the ice is such that the entire continent"},{"time":27000,"text":"sags below sea level, beneath its weight."},{"time":30000,"text":"Yet, the ice of Antarctica"},{"time":32000,"text":"is a calendar of climate change."},{"time":34000,"text":"It records the annual rise and fall"},{"time":36000,"text":"of greenhouse gases and temperatures"},{"time":38000,"text":"going back before the onset of the last ice ages."},{"time":41000,"text":"Nowhere on Earth"},{"time":43000,"text":"offers us such a perfect record."},{"time":46000,"text":"And here, scientists are drilling"},{"time":48000,"text":"into the past of our planet"},{"time":50000,"text":"to find clues to the future"},{"time":52000,"text":"of climate change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54000,"text":"This past January,"},{"time":56000,"text":"I traveled to a place called WAIS Divide,"},{"time":58000,"text":"about 600 miles from the South Pole."},{"time":60000,"text":"It is the best place on the planet, many say,"},{"time":63000,"text":"to study the history of climate change."},{"time":65000,"text":"There, about 45 scientists from the University of Wisconsin,"},{"time":68000,"text":"the Desert Research Institute in Nevada and others"},{"time":71000,"text":"have been working to answer a central question"},{"time":73000,"text":"about global warming."},{"time":75000,"text":"What is the exact relationship"},{"time":77000,"text":"between levels of greenhouse gases"},{"time":80000,"text":"and planetary temperatures?"},{"time":82000,"text":"It's urgent work. We know that temperatures are rising."},{"time":85000,"text":"This past May was the warmest worldwide on record."},{"time":88000,"text":"And we know that levels of greenhouse gases are rising too."},{"time":91000,"text":"What we don't know"},{"time":93000,"text":"is the exact, precise, immediate"},{"time":95000,"text":"impact of these changes"},{"time":97000,"text":"on natural climate patterns --"},{"time":99000,"text":"winds, ocean currents,"},{"time":101000,"text":"precipitation rates, cloud formation,"},{"time":104000,"text":"things that bear on the health and well-being"},{"time":106000,"text":"of billions of people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109000,"text":"Their entire camp, every item of gear,"},{"time":112000,"text":"was ferried 885 miles"},{"time":114000,"text":"from McMurdo Station,"},{"time":116000,"text":"the main U.S. supply base"},{"time":118000,"text":"on the coast of Antarctica."},{"time":120000,"text":"WAIS Divide itself though,"},{"time":122000,"text":"is a circle of tents in the snow."},{"time":125000,"text":"In blizzard winds, the crew sling ropes between the tents"},{"time":128000,"text":"so that people can feel their way safely"},{"time":131000,"text":"to the nearest ice house"},{"time":133000,"text":"and to the nearest outhouse."},{"time":135000,"text":"It snows so heavily there,"},{"time":137000,"text":"the installation was almost immediately buried."},{"time":139000,"text":"Indeed, the researchers picked this site"},{"time":142000,"text":"because ice and snow accumulates here"},{"time":144000,"text":"10 times faster than anywhere else in Antarctica."},{"time":147000,"text":"They have to dig themselves out every day."},{"time":150000,"text":"It makes for an exotic"},{"time":152000,"text":"and chilly commute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":156000,"text":"But under the surface"},{"time":158000,"text":"is a hive of industrial activity"},{"time":161000,"text":"centered around an eight-million-dollar drill assembly."},{"time":164000,"text":"Periodically, this drill, like a biopsy needle,"},{"time":167000,"text":"plunges thousands of feet deep into the ice"},{"time":170000,"text":"to extract a marrow of gases"},{"time":172000,"text":"and isotopes for analysis."},{"time":175000,"text":"Ten times a day, they extract"},{"time":177000,"text":"the 10-foot long cylinder of compressed ice crystals"},{"time":179000,"text":"that contain the unsullied air and trace chemicals"},{"time":182000,"text":"laid down by snow,"},{"time":184000,"text":"season after season for thousands of years."},{"time":189000,"text":"It's really a time machine."},{"time":191000,"text":"At the peak of activity earlier this year,"},{"time":194000,"text":"the researchers lowered the drill"},{"time":197000,"text":"an extra hundred feet deeper into the ice every day"},{"time":200000,"text":"and another 365 years"},{"time":202000,"text":"deeper into the past."},{"time":205000,"text":"Periodically, they remove"},{"time":207000,"text":"a cylinder of ice,"},{"time":209000,"text":"like gamekeepers popping a spent shotgun shell"},{"time":211000,"text":"from the barrel of a drill."},{"time":215000,"text":"They inspect it, they check it for cracks,"},{"time":217000,"text":"for drill damage, for spalls, for chips."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221000,"text":"More importantly,"},{"time":223000,"text":"they prepare it for inspection and analysis"},{"time":225000,"text":"by 27 independent laboratories"},{"time":227000,"text":"in the United States and Europe,"},{"time":229000,"text":"who will examine it for 40 different trace chemicals"},{"time":231000,"text":"related to climate,"},{"time":233000,"text":"some in parts per quadrillion."},{"time":236000,"text":"Yes, I said that with a Q, quadrillion."},{"time":239000,"text":"They cut the cylinders up into three-foot sections"},{"time":241000,"text":"for easier handling and shipment"},{"time":243000,"text":"back to these labs,"},{"time":245000,"text":"some 8,000 miles from the drill site."},{"time":248000,"text":"Each cylinder"},{"time":250000,"text":"is a parfait of time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253000,"text":"This ice formed as snow"},{"time":256000,"text":"15,800 years ago,"},{"time":259000,"text":"when our ancestors were daubing themselves with paint"},{"time":262000,"text":"and considering the radical new technology"},{"time":265000,"text":"of the alphabet."},{"time":268000,"text":"Bathed in polarized light"},{"time":270000,"text":"and cut in cross-section,"},{"time":272000,"text":"this ancient ice reveals itself"},{"time":274000,"text":"as a mosaic of colors,"},{"time":276000,"text":"each one showing how conditions at depth in the ice"},{"time":279000,"text":"have affected this material"},{"time":282000,"text":"at depths where pressures can reach"},{"time":285000,"text":"a ton per square inch."},{"time":288000,"text":"Every year, it begins with a snowflake,"},{"time":291000,"text":"and by digging into fresh snow,"},{"time":293000,"text":"we can see how this process is ongoing today."},{"time":296000,"text":"This wall of undisturbed snow,"},{"time":298000,"text":"back-lit by sunlight,"},{"time":300000,"text":"shows the striations of winter and summer snow,"},{"time":303000,"text":"layer upon layer."},{"time":307000,"text":"Each storm scours the atmosphere,"},{"time":310000,"text":"washing out dust, soot,"},{"time":313000,"text":"trace chemicals,"},{"time":315000,"text":"and depositing them on the snow pack"},{"time":318000,"text":"year after year,"},{"time":320000,"text":"millennia after millennia,"},{"time":322000,"text":"creating a kind of periodic table of elements"},{"time":324000,"text":"that at this point"},{"time":326000,"text":"is more than 11,000 feet thick."},{"time":329000,"text":"From this, we can detect an extraordinary number of things."},{"time":334000,"text":"We can see the calcium"},{"time":336000,"text":"from the world's deserts,"},{"time":338000,"text":"soot from distant wildfires,"},{"time":340000,"text":"methane as an indicator of the strength of a Pacific monsoon,"},{"time":343000,"text":"all wafted on winds from warmer latitudes"},{"time":346000,"text":"to this remote and very cold place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349000,"text":"Most importantly,"},{"time":351000,"text":"these cylinders and this snow"},{"time":353000,"text":"trap air."},{"time":355000,"text":"Each cylinder is about 10 percent ancient air,"},{"time":358000,"text":"a pristine time capsule"},{"time":360000,"text":"of greenhouse gases -- carbon dioxide,"},{"time":362000,"text":"methane, nitrous oxide --"},{"time":364000,"text":"all unchanged from the day that snow formed"},{"time":367000,"text":"and first fell."},{"time":369000,"text":"And this is the object of their scrutiny."},{"time":372000,"text":"But don't we already know"},{"time":374000,"text":"what we need to know about greenhouse gases?"},{"time":376000,"text":"Why do we need to study this anymore?"},{"time":378000,"text":"Don't we already know how they affect temperatures?"},{"time":380000,"text":"Don't we already know the consequences"},{"time":383000,"text":"of a changing climate on our settled civilization?"},{"time":386000,"text":"The truth is, we only know the outlines,"},{"time":389000,"text":"and what we don't completely understand,"},{"time":391000,"text":"we can't properly fix."},{"time":393000,"text":"Indeed, we run the risk of making things worse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396000,"text":"Consider, the single most successful"},{"time":399000,"text":"international environmental effort of the 20th century,"},{"time":402000,"text":"the Montreal Protocol,"},{"time":404000,"text":"in which the nations of Earth banded together to protect the planet"},{"time":407000,"text":"from the harmful effects of ozone-destroying chemicals"},{"time":410000,"text":"used at that time"},{"time":412000,"text":"in air conditioners, refrigerators and other cooling devices."},{"time":415000,"text":"We banned those chemicals,"},{"time":418000,"text":"and we replaced them, unknowingly,"},{"time":420000,"text":"with other substances"},{"time":422000,"text":"that, molecule per molecule,"},{"time":424000,"text":"are a hundred times more potent"},{"time":426000,"text":"as heat-trapping, greenhouse gases"},{"time":428000,"text":"than carbon dioxide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431000,"text":"This process requires"},{"time":433000,"text":"extraordinary precautions."},{"time":436000,"text":"The scientists must insure"},{"time":438000,"text":"that the ice is not contaminated."},{"time":440000,"text":"Moreover, in this 8,000-mile journey,"},{"time":442000,"text":"they have to insure this ice doesn't melt."},{"time":444000,"text":"Imagine juggling a snowball across the tropics."},{"time":448000,"text":"They have to, in fact,"},{"time":450000,"text":"make sure this ice never gets warmer"},{"time":452000,"text":"than about 20 degrees below zero,"},{"time":454000,"text":"otherwise, the key gases inside it will dissipate."},{"time":457000,"text":"So, in the coldest place on Earth,"},{"time":460000,"text":"they work inside a refrigerator."},{"time":463000,"text":"As they handle the ice, in fact,"},{"time":465000,"text":"they keep an extra pair of gloves warming in an oven,"},{"time":467000,"text":"so that, when their work gloves freeze"},{"time":469000,"text":"and their fingers stiffen,"},{"time":471000,"text":"they can don a fresh pair."},{"time":473000,"text":"They work against the clock and against the thermometer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476000,"text":"So far, they've packed up"},{"time":478000,"text":"about 4,500 feet of ice cores"},{"time":482000,"text":"for shipment back to the United States."},{"time":484000,"text":"This past season,"},{"time":486000,"text":"they manhandled them across the ice"},{"time":488000,"text":"to waiting aircraft."},{"time":490000,"text":"The 109th Air National Guard"},{"time":493000,"text":"flew the most recent shipment of ice"},{"time":495000,"text":"back to the coast of Antarctica,"},{"time":497000,"text":"where it was boarded onto a freighter,"},{"time":500000,"text":"shipped across the tropics to California,"},{"time":503000,"text":"unloaded, put on a truck,"},{"time":505000,"text":"driven across the desert"},{"time":507000,"text":"to the National Ice Core Laboratory in Denver, Colorado,"},{"time":509000,"text":"where, as we speak,"},{"time":511000,"text":"scientists are now slicing this material up"},{"time":513000,"text":"for samples, for analysis,"},{"time":515000,"text":"to be distributed"},{"time":517000,"text":"to the laboratories around the country"},{"time":519000,"text":"and in Europe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522000,"text":"Antarctica was this planet's"},{"time":525000,"text":"last empty quarter --"},{"time":527000,"text":"the blind spot"},{"time":529000,"text":"in our expanding vision of the world."},{"time":531000,"text":"Early explorers"},{"time":533000,"text":"sailed off the edge of the map,"},{"time":535000,"text":"and they found a place"},{"time":537000,"text":"where the normal rules of time and temperature"},{"time":539000,"text":"seem suspended."},{"time":543000,"text":"Here, the ice seems a living presence."},{"time":546000,"text":"The wind that rubs against it"},{"time":548000,"text":"gives it voice."},{"time":551000,"text":"It is a voice of experience."},{"time":554000,"text":"It is a voice we should heed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":560000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}